Function# vmnet_network_create_with_serialization(_:_:)

Mac Catalyst 13.0+macOS 26.0+

```
func vmnet_network_create_with_serialization(
    _ network: xpc_object_t,
    _ status: UnsafeMutablePointer<vmnet_return_t>?
) -> vmnet_network_ref?
```

## [ Parameters ](/documentation/vmnet/vmnet_network_create_with_serialization(_:_:)#parameters)

`network`The xpc object from which to create the network

`status`Optional output parameter, returns status.

## [Return Value](/documentation/vmnet/vmnet_network_create_with_serialization(_:_:)#return-value)

Network object in `vmnet_network_ref`, NULL otherwise. `status` will contain the error code.

## [Discussion](/documentation/vmnet/vmnet_network_create_with_serialization(_:_:)#discussion)

Creates a vmnet_network from an xpc object obtained from `vmnet_network_copy_serialization`.
